verses.verse: To the chief <S%H5329>Musician,<s%> A <S%H7892>Song<s%> or <S%H4210>Psalm.<s%> Make a joyful <S%H7321>noise<s%> unto <S%H430>God,<s%> <S%H3605>all<s%> ye lands: <S%H776><s%>
Sing <S%H2167>forth<s%> the <S%H3519>honor<s%> of his <S%H8034>name:<s%> <S%H7760>make<s%> his <S%H8416>praise<s%> <S%H3519>glorious.<s%>

Say <S%H559><s%> unto <S%H430>God,<s%> <S%H4100>How<s%> <S%H3372>terrible<s%> art thou in thy <S%H4639>works!<s%> through the <S%H7230>greatness<s%> of thy <S%H5797>power<s%> shall thine <S%H341>enemies<s%> <S%H3584>submit<s%> themselves unto thee.
All <S%H3605><s%> the <S%H776>earth<s%> shall <S%H7812>worship<s%> thee, and shall <S%H2167>sing<s%> unto thee; they shall <S%H2167>sing<s%> to thy <S%H8034>name.<s%> <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>

Come <S%H1980><s%> and <S%H7200>see<s%> the <S%H4659>works<s%> of <S%H430>God:<s%> he is <S%H3372>terrible<s%> in his <S%H5949>doing<s%> <S%H5921>toward<s%> the <S%H1121>children<s%> of <S%H120>men.<s%>

He <S%H2015>turned<s%> the <S%H3220>sea<s%> into <S%H3004>dry<s%> land: they <S%H5674>went<s%> through the <S%H5104>flood<s%> on <S%H7272>foot:<s%> <S%H8033>there<s%> did we <S%H8055>rejoice<s%> in him.

He <S%H4910>ruleth<s%> by his <S%H1369>power<s%> <S%H5769>forever;<s%> his <S%H5869>eyes<s%> <S%H6822>behold<s%> the <S%H1471>nations:<s%> let <S%H408>not<s%> the <S%H5637>rebellious<s%> <S%H7311>exalt<s%> themselves. <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>
O <S%H1288>bless<s%> our <S%H430>God,<s%> ye <S%H5971>people,<s%> and make the <S%H6963>voice<s%> of his <S%H8416>praise<s%> to be heard: <S%H8085><s%>
Which <S%H7760>holdeth<s%> our <S%H5315>soul<s%> in <S%H2416>life,<s%> and <S%H5414>suffereth<s%> <S%H3808>not<s%> our <S%H7272>feet<s%> to be <S%H4132>moved.<s%>
For <S%H3588><s%> thou, O <S%H430>God,<s%> hast <S%H974>proved<s%> us: thou hast <S%H6884>tried<s%> us, as <S%H3701>silver<s%> is <S%H6884>tried.<s%>
Thou <S%H935>broughtest<s%> us into the <S%H4686>net;<s%> thou <S%H7760>laidst<s%> <S%H4157>affliction<s%> upon our <S%H4975>loins.<s%>

Thou hast caused <S%H582>men<s%> to <S%H7392>ride<s%> over our <S%H7218>heads;<s%> we <S%H935>went<s%> through <S%H784>fire<s%> and through <S%H4325>water:<s%> but thou broughtest us <S%H3318>out<s%> into a <S%H7310>wealthy<s%> place.
I will <S%H935>go<s%> into thy <S%H1004>house<s%> with burnt <S%H5930>offerings:<s%> I will <S%H7999>pay<s%> thee my <S%H5088>vows,<s%>
Which <S%H834><s%> my <S%H8193>lips<s%> have <S%H6475>uttered,<s%> and my <S%H6310>mouth<s%> hath <S%H1696>spoken,<s%> when I was in <S%H6862>trouble.<s%>

I will <S%H5927>offer<s%> unto thee burnt <S%H5930>sacrifices<s%> of <S%H4220>fatlings,<s%> <S%H5973>with<s%> the <S%H7004>incense<s%> of <S%H352>rams;<s%> I will <S%H6213>offer<s%> <S%H1241>bullocks<s%> <S%H5973>with<s%> <S%H6260>goats.<s%> <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>

Come <S%H1980><s%> and <S%H8085>hear,<s%> <S%H3605>all<s%> ye that <S%H3373>fear<s%> <S%H430>God,<s%> and I will <S%H5608>declare<s%> <S%H834>what<s%> he hath <S%H6213>done<s%> for my <S%H5315>soul.<s%>
I <S%H7121>cried<s%> <S%H413>unto<s%> him with my <S%H6310>mouth,<s%> and he was <S%H7318>extolled<s%> <S%H8478>with<s%> my <S%H3956>tongue.<s%>
If <S%H518><s%> I <S%H7200>regard<s%> <S%H205>iniquity<s%> in my <S%H3820>heart,<s%> the <S%H136>Lord<s%> will <S%H3808>not<s%> <S%H8085>hear<s%> me:
But <S%H403>verily<s%> <S%H430>God<s%> hath <S%H8085>heard<s%> me; he hath <S%H7181>attended<s%> to the <S%H6963>voice<s%> of my <S%H8605>prayer.<s%>
Blessed <S%H1288><s%> be <S%H430>God,<s%> <S%H834>which<s%> hath <S%H3808>not<s%> turned <S%H5493>away<s%> my <S%H8605>prayer,<s%> nor his <S%H2617>mercy<s%> <S%H4480>from<s%> <S%H854><s%> me.
